<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="506" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1691,1968]" pageId="16" pageNumber="506">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1799,1824]" pageId="16" pageNumber="506">Remarks:</emphasis>
We found this species in 
<collectingRegion box="[608,708,1799,1824]" country="China" name="Guangxi" pageId="16" pageNumber="506">Guangxi</collectingRegion>
; this species is allied to 
<taxonomicName authority="Lv et Zhou" authorityName="Lv &amp; Zhao &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="2018" box="[981,1334,1799,1824]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="506" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhangyejunianus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[981,1198,1800,1824]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="506">S. zhangyejunianus</emphasis>
Lv et Zhou
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1346,1436,1799,1824]" pageId="16" pageNumber="506" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1346,1436,1799,1824]" pageId="16" pageNumber="506">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
in most aspects, but it is distinguishable from the latter by the following characteristics: punctures on pronotum less confluent, smaller elytra spot, spot not extending to the lateral margin of elytra and aedeagal median lobe (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE17" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1129,1151]" captionTargetBox="[359,1227,194,1098]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[340,1247,193,1108]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE17. Stenus perroti Puthz, 1981. A. aedeagus;B. male sterniteVIII; C. male sternite IX; D. male tergite X; Scale bar = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1199946/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="506">Figs. 17A</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation box="[235,284,1908,1932]" captionStart="FIGURE18" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1948,1970]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,392,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,391,1908]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE18. Stenus perroti Puthz, 1981. A. aedeagus;B. male sterniteVIII; C. male sternite IX; D. male tergite X; Scale bar = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1199948/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="506">18A</figureCitation>
) with more acutely triangular apical sclerotized area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
